[7.] There are, of course, many other examples of punishments for base and abhorrent mendacity which will strike one at first glance. But, as we have already touched upon briefly, men confirmed by faith at the apex of virtue have themselves defined what makes lies most abominable, namely that a lying mouth slays the liar's soul, moves God Almighty to wrath, and quickly compels Him to take bitter offense. The man who lies wrongfully does not deign to consider that he is damnably defrauding his soul of rest for all eternity.
